abstract: LAS VEGAS, Nev., March 20 (AP)  Jo Ann Washam carded a four-underpar 68 today to take a two-stroke lead after the opening round of the $200,000 Ladies' Professional Golf Association national pro-am tournament.

SHE'S an actress, an artist, an aviator, a barber, a cranberry  sorter. She dances, doctors, gambles, models, mothers, nurses. She toils in the house, in the factory, on the farm, in the pulpit, in the bordello. She sells goods, brands cattle, types letters, walks tightropes, handles switchboards and swallows swords.

abstract: PRINCETON NOW at the McCarter Theater until next Sunday, James McLure's "1959 Pink Thunderbird" is the umbrella title  for two comedies that keep the sexes separate but equal. The author's men hold forth in "Lone Star," the first play, and his women in "Laundry and Bourbon," the second half of the bill.
